<subSubSection id="C3106564FF82FFEBC058FDD3CFF46B93" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB536EFFF82FFEBC058FDD3CFF46B93" blockId="5.[88,614,487,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
DIAGNOSIS: Members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC1B5FDD3CD4E6ABC" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[415,518,636,660]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC1B5FDD3CD4E6ABC" box="[415,518,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from all other leiognathids by the combination of an expansive translucent triangular, cornucopia-shaped or trapezoidal patch on the flank in males, a greatly elongate and feeble second dorsal-fin spine (more pronounced in males), and a pigmentation pattern on the dorsal flank comprising speckles and vermiculate markings or broad oblong markings that occasionally form open circular patterns.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3106564FF82FFEBC058FC6DCDAD6B32" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB536EFFF82FFEBC058FC6DCE796EF2" blockId="5.[88,614,487,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
REMARKS: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC0D4FC6DCE2D6BF2" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[254,357,962,986]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC0D4FC6DCE2D6BF2" box="[254,357,962,986]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC072FC70CE306BDF" author="Fowler, H. W." box="[88,376,991,1015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="495 - 560" refId="ref5784" refString="Fowler, H. W. 1904. A collection of fishes from Sumatra. Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia 12 (4): 495 - 560, pls. 7 - 28." type="journal article" year="1904">Fowler (1904: 516–517)</bibRefCitation>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC072FC52CFA86C3D" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[88,224,1021,1045]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC072FC52CFA86C3D" box="[88,224,1021,1045]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to encompass his newly described species 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC081FBB4CD296C1A" authority="Fowler, 1904" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[171,609,1050,1075]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vermiculatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC081FBB4CE8C6C1B" box="[171,452,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Leiognathus vermiculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC1E1FBB5CD296C1A" author="Fowler, H. W." box="[459,609,1050,1074]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="495 - 560" refId="ref5784" refString="Fowler, H. W. 1904. A collection of fishes from Sumatra. Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia 12 (4): 495 - 560, pls. 7 - 28." type="journal article" year="1904">Fowler, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC0BEFB97CE816C78" authority="Fowler, 1904" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[148,457,1080,1104]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virgatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC0BEFB97CE5E6C78" box="[148,278,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">L. virgatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC10DFB97CE816C78" author="Fowler, H. W." box="[295,457,1080,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="495 - 560" refId="ref5784" refString="Fowler, H. W. 1904. A collection of fishes from Sumatra. Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia 12 (4): 495 - 560, pls. 7 - 28." type="journal article" year="1904">Fowler, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC1F4FB97CFF86C46" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virgatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC1F4FB97CFF86C46" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Leiognathus virgatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a deep-bodied species, was subsequently synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC1B2FBDCCD686CA3" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[408,544,1139,1163]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC1B2FBDCCD686CA3" box="[408,544,1139,1163]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC072FB3ECE4D6C81" box="[88,261,1169,1193]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Photopectoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC072FB3ECE4D6C81" box="[88,261,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Photopectoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC134FB3ECD2E6C81" authority="(Valenciennes, 1835)" baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[286,614,1169,1193]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Photopectoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bindus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC134FB3ECE2D6C81" box="[286,357,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">bindus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC151FB3ECD166C81" author="Valenciennes, A." box="[379,606,1169,1193]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="60 - 103" refId="ref6741" refString="Valenciennes, A. 1835. Des Equula. In G. Cuvier and A. Valenciennes (editors), Histoire naturelle des poissons. Vol. 10: 60 - 103, pls. 283 - 284. Paris: F. G. Levrault." type="journal article" year="1835">Valenciennes, 1835</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC0BEFB01CEAE6CEE" author="Woodland, D. J. &amp; S. Premcharoen &amp; A. S. Cabanban" box="[148,486,1198,1222]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="2792 - 2823" refId="ref6815" refString="Woodland, D. J., S. Premcharoen, and A. S. Cabanban. 2001. Leiognathidae: Slipmouths (ponyfishes). In K. E. Carpenter and V. H. Niem (editors), Species identification guide for fishery purposes. The living marine resources of the Western Central Pacific. Bony fishes part 3 (Menidae to Pomacentridae), 2792 - 2823. Rome: FAO." type="book chapter" year="2001">Woodland et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC072FB63CE366CCC" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[88,382,1228,1252]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vermiculatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC072FB63CE366CCC" box="[88,382,1228,1252]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Leiognathus vermiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymized with 
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC0B3FB46CFFA6D29" box="[153,178,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">L.</emphasis>
(now 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC121FB46CE3A6D29" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[267,370,1257,1281]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC121FB46CE3A6D29" box="[267,370,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC1A1FB46CEA36D29" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[395,491,1257,1281]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leuciscus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC1A1FB46CEA36D29" box="[395,491,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">leuciscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC20DFB46CE596D37" author="Jones, G." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="559 - 613" refId="ref6143" refString="Jones, G. 1985. Revision of the Australian species of the fish family Leiognathidae. Australian Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research 36: 559 - 613." type="journal article" year="1985">Jones (1985: 590–591)</bibRefCitation>
, a synonymy further corroborated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC0C8FA8BCE986D14" author="Sparks, J. S." box="[226,464,1316,1340]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref6501" refString="Sparks, J. S. 2006 b. A new species of ponyfish (Teleostei: Leiognathidae: Photoplagios) from Madagascar, with a phylogeny for Photoplagios and comments on the status of Equula lineolata Valenciennes. American Museum Novitates 3526: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2006">Sparks (2006b: 13)</bibRefCitation>
. Herein we elevate 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC084FAEDCE5D6D72" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[174,277,1346,1370]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC084FAEDCE5D6D72" box="[174,277,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a strongly supported monophyletic assemblage (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC16CFAF0CD526D5F" author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap &amp; W. L. Smith" box="[326,538,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="305 - 327" refId="ref6599" refString="Sparks, J. S., P. V. Dunlap, and W. L. Smith. 2005. Evolution and diversification of a sexually dimorphic luminescent system in ponyfishes (Teleostei: Leiognathidae), including diagnoses for two new genera. Cladistics 21: 305 - 327." type="journal article" year="2005">Sparks et al., 2005</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1) comprising three nominal species, to generic rank. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC088FA34CE416D9B" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[162,265,1435,1459]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC088FA34CE416D9B" box="[162,265,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread genus, with members’ distributions spanning nearly the entire geographic range of the family. Members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC0C4FA5CCE1D6E23" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[238,341,1523,1547]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC0C4FA5CCE1D6E23" box="[238,341,1523,1547]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are sexually dimorphic with respect to light-organ volume and shape, with those of males being considerably larger than similarly sized conspecific females. Males also possess an expansive translucent triangular flank patch and corresponding clearing of the guanine-lined gas bladder, features lacking entirely in females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB536EFFF82FFEBC29AFF7CCDAD6B32" blockId="5.[662,1188,211,794]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC362FF7CCCE768C3" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[840,943,211,235]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC362FF7CCCE768C3" box="[840,943,211,235]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can easily be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC31BFF5ECC896921" box="[817,961,241,265]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Photoplagios" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC31BFF5ECC896921" box="[817,961,241,265]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Photoplagios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to which they were formerly assigned (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC354FEA1CB24690E" author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap &amp; W. L. Smith" box="[894,1132,270,294]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="305 - 327" refId="ref6599" refString="Sparks, J. S., P. V. Dunlap, and W. L. Smith. 2005. Evolution and diversification of a sexually dimorphic luminescent system in ponyfishes (Teleostei: Leiognathidae), including diagnoses for two new genera. Cladistics 21: 305 - 327." type="journal article" year="2005">Sparks et al., 2005</bibRefCitation>
), by pigmentation pattern on the dorsal flank (vermiculate and highly mottled in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC417FEE6CBEC6949" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[1085,1188,329,353]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC417FEE6CBEC6949" box="[1085,1188,329,353]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. much larger and more sparse oval blotches in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC29EFE2BCC0C69B4" box="[692,836,388,412]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Photoplagios" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC29EFE2BCC0C69B4" box="[692,836,388,412]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Photoplagios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see Sparks and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC421FE2CCD876991" author="Chakrabarty, P. &amp; J. S. Sparks" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref5427" refString="Chakrabarty, P., and J. S. Sparks. 2007. Phylogeny and taxonomic revision of Nuchequula Whitley 1932 (Teleostei: Leiognathidae), with the description of a new species. American Museum Novitates 3588: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="2007">Chakrabarty, 2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1), length of the second dorsal-fin spine (markedly elongate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC3D9FE10CB1269FF" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[1011,1114,447,471]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC3D9FE10CB1269FF" box="[1011,1114,447,471]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and degree of sexual dimorphism and morphology of the light organ (dorsal lobes of males moderately enlarged in males and extending only slightly into the gas bladder chamber in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC2BCFDFDCDB56A42" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[662,765,594,618]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC2BCFDFDCDB56A42" box="[662,765,594,618]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Equulites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. dorsal lobes of males greatly enlarged and extending posteriorly well into the gas bladder chamber in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D6CFF82FFEBC429FD22CBDB6A8D" box="[1027,1171,653,677]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Photoplagios" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97EEAFDFF82FFEBC429FD22CBDB6A8D" box="[1027,1171,653,677]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Photoplagios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Sparks and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B1EFF82FFEBC337FD05CB7C6AEA" author="Chakrabarty, P. &amp; J. S. Sparks" box="[797,1076,682,706]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref5427" refString="Chakrabarty, P., and J. S. Sparks. 2007. Phylogeny and taxonomic revision of Nuchequula Whitley 1932 (Teleostei: Leiognathidae), with the description of a new species. American Museum Novitates 3588: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="2007">Chakrabarty (2007: 627)</bibRefCitation>
present a number of diagnostic species-level features to distinguish members of this clade from congeners.
</paragraph>
